{
  "texts": [
    "The adjustments are incremental to make it easier for the algorithm to find a global minimum instead of a local minimum of the loss function.",
    "The amount of parameter adjustment is a hyperparameter called the learning rate, empirically set by the model developers.",
    "A proper learning rate helps balance how quickly the model reaches its optimal state and the accuracy of the final model.",
    "A high learning rate can achieve faster training, but the model can overshoot the optimal solution, leading to poor performance.",
    "Backpropagation uses a method called stochastic gradient descent (SGD{XE \"SGD:stochastic gradient descent\"}) that adds randomness to the process which further prevents the error from being stuck in a local minimum."
  ]
}